               <physDesc>
                  <p>(1) It would seem that the first 712 stanzas were written by a different hand
                     than that of Ampalavāṇavāttiyār. However, this is not confirmed by the
                     palaeographical analysis of the manuscript. (2) The expression ivai eḻutiṉa
                     naṉmaikku is unclear, in particular what preposition should be understood in
                     the relative participle eḻutiṉa (see CNM D1063 for a similar case). (3) Line
                     [273v2] has the unidentified sign at its end that is written outside the block
                     of the text and which we have transcribed with a question mark. (3) The day of
                     the month recorded in the date (8) is wrong (it should be 7): the mistake was
                     spotted and corrected – and the date could be converted into the Gregorian
                     calendar – only thanks to the mention in the date of the “Festival of
                     Mahālakṣmī” (makālaṭcuminoṉpum), which, being celebrated on the second Friday
                     of the bright fortnight of the lunar month of Śrāvaṇa, provided us with
                     additional and decisive calendrical elements. </p>
               </physDesc>
